  "notes": "Volapük — constructed international auxiliary language (Johann Martin Schleyer, 1879/1880), here in its modern reformed form (Volapük nulik, Arie de Jong 1931). Phonemic one-letter-one-sound orthography over the 27-letter alphabet a ä b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p r s t u ü v w x y z. ⟨c⟩ = /tʃ/, ⟨j⟩ = /ʃ/, ⟨z⟩ = /ts/, ⟨x⟩ = the cluster /ks/, ⟨y⟩ = /j/. Voiced variants ([dʒ], [ʒ], [dz]) are permitted realisations. Stress is always on the final vowel of a polysyllabic word.",
  "timespan": {
    "start_year": 1879,
    "end_year": null
  }
